						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying behind the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>1059 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record contains two dates 1) <hi rend="bold">Śaka 980, Vi[ḷaṁbi], Vaisakha-puṇṇame</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1058 A.D., April 11,</hi> the details being insufficient for verification. 2) <hi rend="bold">Śaka [981], Vaiśākha-Puṇṇame, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1059 A.D., April 29, Thursday, f.d.t. ·43.</hi></p>						

						<p>The extant portion refers to a Telugu-Chōḷa chief. All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
